Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.39,0:01:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The invasion of the royal capital\Nwas orchestrated by Eri Nakamura,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.10,0:01:46.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who had a shared interest with the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.52,0:01:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using her natural talent in necromancy,\Nshe used the corpse of the female demon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.15,0:01:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that she encountered in the Orcus\NGreat Labyrinth to carry a message.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.07,0:01:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is how she managed\Nto get in contact with the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.95,0:02:04.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, in exchange for helping\Nthe demons access the capital
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.33,0:02:08.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and murdering the knighthood\Nand her classmates,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.04,0:02:12.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,she asked for freedom\Nfor herself and Kouki Amanogawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.96,0:02:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it is believed that she did not\Nmurder all of her classmates at once
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.26,0:02:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because her unique magic,\N"Spirit Binding,"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.43,0:02:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can only be used one at a time,\Nimmediately after the target's death.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.35,0:02:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The invasion was a failure, and Eri\NNakamura escaped with the demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.73,0:02:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The brainwashing and murder of our king\Nis believed to be the work of the nun
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.40,0:02:42.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the Divine Mountain, who also\Nkidnapped Aiko Hatayama, not Eri Nakamura.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.37,0:02:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, this nun is still missing.\NWe are seeking more information.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.21,0:03:02.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Out of the transferees, we've lost\NDaisuke Hiyama, Reiichi Kondo, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.31,0:03:09.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Kaori Shirasaki...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.46,0:03:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.79,0:03:35.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aiko-{\i1}san {\i0}is taking a break now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.13,0:03:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.13,0:03:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori will be fine. Please go to Aiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.55,0:03:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yue...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.77,0:03:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:03:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.28,0:04:06.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.03,0:04:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You care about your students more\Nthan anything, and I killed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.04,0:04:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure that's weighing on your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.50,0:04:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, it's not something\NI can easily get over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.46,0:04:24.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What Hiyama-{\i1}kun {\i0}did can't be forgiven,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.09,0:04:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I wanted him to live\Nto atone for his sins, if possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.22,0:04:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I also understand the anger you felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.14,0:04:40.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I have no right\Nto criticize you, Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.11,0:04:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, you just helped. Don't blame\Nyourself as if you did it all on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.78,0:04:47.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.78,0:04:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I helped Tio-{\i1}san {\i0}with the full knowledge\Nthat it could kill them!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.66,0:04:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you regret it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.42,0:04:57.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.75,0:05:01.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew what I was doing with Tio-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.38,0:05:05.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't let the church\Ncontinue doing what it was doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.55,0:05:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.97,0:05:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had to stop them from doing\Nhorrible things to my students.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.81,0:05:18.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I... I don't have any regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.73,0:05:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, will you continue\Nto be our sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.03,0:05:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.86,0:05:32.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you can continue to be our sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.29,0:05:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can I make a very selfish request?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.04,0:05:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Selfish request?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.83,0:05:45.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to keep feeling guilty.\NI want you to carry that weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you fight properly,\Ncarry the weight properly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.22,0:05:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,worry properly, and complain properly,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.89,0:05:57.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that's very human, blindingly so.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.02,0:06:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are emotions I can no longer feel,\Nso you can be my example
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.73,0:06:05.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of what it means to be human.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.44,0:06:10.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep my eyes on you.\NThat way, when I make it back to Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.24,0:06:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can live a proper, human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.50,0:06:17.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.33,0:06:24.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That said, if you're in too much pain\Nand feel like you're about to break,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.17,0:06:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there's nobody else to rely on...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.22,0:06:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, you can cry on my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.93,0:06:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You... You're such a...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.27,0:06:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, then, I'll take you up on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.27,0:06:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.33,0:07:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.05,0:07:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem tired from\Nyour workout, Kouki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.97,0:07:16.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lily... No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.31,0:07:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, on the other hand, haven't slept much\Nat all these past five days, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.98,0:07:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still all right. It's a lot of work,\Nbut the people who are truly hurt
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.07,0:07:29.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are the citizens who've lost\Ntheir loved ones or livelihoods.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.86,0:07:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you've also lost your father--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.03,0:07:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.12,0:07:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.54,0:07:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is Shizuku?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.41,0:07:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.83,0:07:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She behaves normally most of the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.84,0:07:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but oftentimes,\Nshe'll look up and keep staring.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.34,0:07:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's waiting for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.97,0:07:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I can't trust Nagumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.80,0:07:59.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm actually hoping\NShizuku doesn't see them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.48,0:08:14.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kouki-{\i1}san{\i0}! Up there!\NIs something coming from above?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.32,0:08:16.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.41,0:08:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, watch out!\NSomething's coming from above!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.30,0:08:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.43,0:08:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Yaegashi. Good, you're alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.48,0:08:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}, where's Kaori?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.03,0:08:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why isn't Kaori here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.99,0:08:55.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, well, she'll be here any moment now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.03,0:09:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, well, she looks\Na little different now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.45,0:09:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's totally not my fault,\Nso don't get mad at me, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.58,0:09:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, what? What is it? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.96,0:09:09.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm worried now.\NWhat are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.59,0:09:11.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you do to Kaori?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.09,0:09:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.72,0:09:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This voice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.80,0:09:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catch me, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.10,0:09:24.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.37,0:09:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.12,0:09:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Kouki!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.75,0:09:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shizuku?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.84,0:10:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.43,0:10:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori, is that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.35,0:10:07.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! It's me, Kaori!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.48,0:10:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori Shirasaki,\NShizuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}'s best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.23,0:10:14.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I might look a little different,\Nbut I'm very much alive!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.57,0:10:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.00,0:10:26.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.42,0:10:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I worried you.\NI'm fine. Everything's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.63,0:10:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad, I'm so glad...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.81,0:10:52.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.69,0:10:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To explain simply,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.44,0:10:56.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we used magic to protect Kaori's soul
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.82,0:11:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and implanted it in Noint's repaired body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.82,0:11:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. I don't get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.91,0:11:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Shizuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}. We learned\Nbefore that the magic we normally use
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.21,0:11:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is an inferior copy of the magic from\Nthe era called the God's Age, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.63,0:11:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the magic that's mentioned in the\Ncreation mythology of this world, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.97,0:11:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The magic that can work\Non a more fundamental level,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.97,0:11:25.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,unlike the elemental magic we use now...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.64,0:11:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.85,0:11:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,are you saying Nagumo-{\i1}kun {\i0}can use\NGod's Age magic to manipulate souls?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.36,0:11:40.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you used that to protect Kaori's soul\Nfrom death and put it in another body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.20,0:11:43.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I knew you'd get it, Shizuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.37,0:11:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why that body?\NWas Kaori's original body ruined?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.37,0:11:52.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We fixed Kaori's body perfectly, and we\Ncould have put the soul back there, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.92,0:11:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.54,0:11:56.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.13,0:11:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.42,0:12:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.51,0:12:05.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know Kaori.\NShe won't stop once she starts asking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.43,0:12:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori's original body is stored\Nin a frozen state using magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.52,0:12:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She can go back to it whenever she wants.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.56,0:12:16.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.36,0:12:22.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori always did do the craziest\Nthings, but this one takes the cake.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.86,0:12:25.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I worried you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.03,0:12:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine. You're alive,\Nthat's what matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.29,0:12:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}, Yue-{\i1}san{\i0}, Shea-{\i1}san{\i0}, Tio-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.25,0:12:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much\Nfor saving my best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.96,0:12:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will never forget this debt.\NIf there is anything I can do, please ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.30,0:12:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will do whatever it takes\Nto pay you back..
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.51,0:12:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're so righteous, as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.98,0:12:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, don't take it so seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.35,0:12:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saved our friend, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.65,0:13:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That said, you did care\Nabout my feelings, too
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.28,0:13:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and used your precious medicine on Kouki.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.57,0:13:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you broke down, Yaegashi, that\Nwould make Kaori annoying to deal with.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.95,0:13:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Annoying? That's mean, Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.29,0:13:16.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.96,0:13:22.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to a certain sensei,\NI should avoid living a sad life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.55,0:13:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do everything,\Nbut I can do some things.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.55,0:13:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.18,0:13:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.98,0:13:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying we've been pawns\Nin the god's game this whole time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.77,0:13:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell us sooner?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.27,0:13:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I told you, would you have believed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.61,0:13:50.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That god is crazy and\Nwhat you all are doing is meaningless.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.28,0:13:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not only would you have not believed me,\Nyou probably would have criticized me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.00,0:13:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... if we're going to be fighting\Nalongside each other from now on...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.96,0:14:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa, hold on. I'm not going\Nto go after the guy to fight him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.00,0:14:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, you don't care what happens\Nto the people of this world?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.34,0:14:12.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any power to wield\Nfor people whom I've never met.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.10,0:14:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?! You're stronger than me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.64,0:14:20.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you have so much power, shouldn't\Nyou be using it to do what's right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.74,0:14:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I have power. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.61,0:14:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you end up with your face in\Nthe dirt at the most important moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.74,0:14:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.87,0:14:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't do things because\Nyou have the power to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.83,0:14:42.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have to want to accomplish something,\Nthen gather and wield power to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.46,0:14:45.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your willpower is just too weak for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.28,0:15:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.45,0:15:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Yue?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.87,0:15:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to leave them like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.20,0:15:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They have their sensei with them,\Nit should be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.00,0:15:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we leave them now,\Nare you going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.38,0:15:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.01,0:15:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.63,0:15:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Shizuku-{\i1}chan{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.26,0:15:34.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kaori, can we sit with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.39,0:15:35.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.85,0:15:41.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, great sister!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.48,0:15:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.52,0:15:47.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}, where are you going next?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.61,0:15:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to a Great Labyrinth, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.32,0:15:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the great forest to the east.\NThe Great Labyrinth is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.16,0:15:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, you will be passing through\Nthe Empire's territory, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.58,0:15:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.58,0:15:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.70,0:16:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, may I come along?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.21,0:16:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.46,0:16:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After the invasion, we have so much\Nwe need to discuss with the Empire.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.30,0:16:14.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We need to meet\Nwith them as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.97,0:16:18.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind taking you along, but\NI'm not going into the imperial capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I definitely won't be joining you\Nwhen you meet the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.10,0:16:26.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I wouldn't ask so much of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.40,0:16:28.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, we're coming along, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.61,0:16:31.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't leave Lily\Nin the hands of someone
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.03,0:16:33.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who doesn't care\Nwhat happens to this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.20,0:16:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll provide protection along the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.41,0:16:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Nagumo won't do anything, then\NI have to be the one to save this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.62,0:16:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To do that, I need power!\NThe power of God's Age magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.08,0:16:48.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I follow you,\NI can get that magic, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.34,0:16:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, I can tell you where it is.\NGo ahead and get it on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.59,0:16:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You, follow me? That'd be such a bother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.80,0:17:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}, didn't you\Nsay that in our current state,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:02.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if we went to the labyrinth,\Nwe'd all immediately die?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.77,0:17:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Uh... I mean, I was useless,\Nbut I was able to pull it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:11.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you'll be fine. Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.20,0:17:17.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.74,0:17:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I join you, too? As a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.04,0:17:27.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just having one God's Age magic\Nwould make a world of a difference
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.04,0:17:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when tackling the other Great Labyrinths.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.13,0:17:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too, Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}. I want to be stronger,\Nso that I can talk to Eri again!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.68,0:17:41.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Nagumo. I want to at least be\Nable to protect myself and my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.52,0:17:44.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.23,0:17:53.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We leave at dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.74,0:17:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.78,0:17:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're definitely clearing\Nthe Great Labyrinth!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.87,0:18:01.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.66,0:18:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hajime-{\i1}san{\i0}, are you sure?\N--As long as we work together...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.54,0:18:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I thought they'd get in the way,\Nbut if coming along can grant them powers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.21,0:18:14.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm starting to think\Nthat's not such a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.05,0:18:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime, so terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.55,0:18:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master is truly great. His thinking\Nis beyond human boundaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.76,0:18:23.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.18,0:18:27.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's trying to use his classmates\Nas meat shields and bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.89,0:18:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.61,0:18:34.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.44,0:18:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.53,0:18:42.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}san{\i0}, say ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.24,0:18:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hajime-{\i1}kun{\i0}...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.33,0:18:47.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too! Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.21,0:18:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master, please eat mine, too. Say ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.34,0:18:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just this once.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.84,0:19:02.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this atmosphere?\NI've never been so uncomfortable.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.19,0:19:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pervert.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.10,0:19:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What? No! Why would you say that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.73,0:19:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just eating normally!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.40,0:19:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're enjoying the taste of Hajime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.74,0:19:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No I'm not! Look at Tio!\NShe's the pervert!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.99,0:19:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at how she's licking\Nthat fork like nobody's watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.83,0:19:32.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tio, stop that immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.67,0:19:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't help it.\NMaster still won't kiss me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.30,0:19:44.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! I remember! Master! I demand a reward!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.51,0:19:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.64,0:19:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I helped protect your sensei.\NI deserve a reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.93,0:19:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.14,0:19:52.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not fair!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.48,0:19:57.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want? I'll warn you,\NI'll only do what I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.98,0:20:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, I won't be unreasonable.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.40,0:20:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want you to brutalize my rear,\Nlike you did when we first met.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.54,0:20:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Denied.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.75,0:20:12.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! That's totally reasonable!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.46,0:20:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want you to pierce my behind with\Na dark, stiff, thick rod, like before!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.38,0:20:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop intentionally inviting\Na misunderstanding!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.55,0:20:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, is it really a misunderstanding?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.85,0:20:28.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not actually lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.01,0:20:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It really did pierce her.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.18,0:20:33.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Nagumo-{\i1}kun {\i0}didn't hold back at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.60,0:20:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime-{\i1}san{\i0}, "misunderstanding"\Nis a bit of stretch.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.65,0:20:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime, you're responsible for\Nher perversion. It can't be avoided.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.74,0:20:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nagumo-{\i1}kun{\i0}...\NWhat did you do to poor Tio-{\i1}san{\i0}...?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.38,0:20:58.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.59,0:21:04.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, Tio. Here's your reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.55,0:21:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go with this one. It's harder,\Nthicker, and heavier than the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.27,0:21:14.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, Master! What I meant was...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.27,0:21:16.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so modest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.98,0:21:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be instantly\Nand eternally satisfied,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.11,0:21:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you won't even have time to moan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.82,0:21:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The master is serious!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.74,0:21:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yue, Shea, Kaori! Please stop Master!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.22,0:21:50.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hajime.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.65,0:22:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today is going to be another long day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.28,0:22:06.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's wrap this journey up\Nquickly and go pick up Myu.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.83,0:22:18.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two are alone again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.71,0:22:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not fair! Why always only Yue?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.64,0:22:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.44,0:22:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Nagumo! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.78,0:22:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're clearing the Great Labyrinth!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.45,0:22:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.53,0:22:53.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You all are too eager.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.41,0:22:56.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nagumo-{\i1}san{\i0}, thank you for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.54,0:22:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.62,0:23:00.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take care of the capital.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.04,0:23:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, please be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.21,0:23:06.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.03,0:23:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, here we go.